then RDA will always give an overestimate of the true MOI.\nObservations have shown that small nonhydrostatic gravity anomalies exist on\nGanymede and Titan. We conclude that nonhydrostatic effects could be present to\nan extent that allows Callisto and Titan to be fully differentiated.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 4 Sep 2013 23:04:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-17"}
