rained than those of younger early-Ts, will anchor our\nunderstanding of the colours of L/T transition brown dwarfs. It is also one of\nthe most massive T dwarfs, just below the hydrogen-burning limit, and all this\nmakes it a prime probe a brown dwarf atmosphere and evolution models.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 5 Sep 2013 07:41:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-17"}
